The example below shows how to configure a Kuberentes service that establishes a connection between a virtual machine that is running a MariaDB server and a virtual machine that is running a database client.

The steps are:

1- Create two VMs; a mariadb server and mariadb client.

2- Label the mariadb-server VM.

3- Create a service of the ClusterIP type.

4- Verify the database connectivity from the mariadb-client VM.


## 1- Create two VMs; a mariadb-server and mariadb-client


Install mariadb-server service on the mariadb-server VM and mysql client on the mariadb-client.

On the mariadb-server VM

```
# virtctl console mariadb-server
```

```
# sudo -i
```

```
# dnf install mariadb-server -y
```

```
# systemctl enable --now mariadb-server
```

```
mysql_secure_installation
```

On the mariadb-client VM

```
# virtctl console mariadb-client
```

```
# sudo -i
```

```
# dnf install mysql telnet -y
```


## 2- Label the mariadb-server VM

```
# oc edit vm mariadb-server
```

```yml
...
spec:
  dataVolumeTemplates:
  ...
  runStrategy: RerunOnFailure
  template:
    metadata:
      creationTimestamp: null
      labels:
        app: mariadb-server
        flavor.template.kubevirt.io/small: "true"
        kubevirt.io/domain: mariadb-server
        kubevirt.io/size: small
        ...
``` 

```
# oc delete vmi 
```

```
# watch oc get vmi,pods -l app=mariadb-server
```

## 3- Create a service of the ClusterIP

Create a service of the ClusterIP type linked to the mariadb-server VM.. Use the _app=mariadb-server_ label for the selector. The service must listen on TCP port _3306_ and forward the traffic to the VM on that port.

```
# virtctl expose vmi mariadb-server --name mariadb \
  --type ClusterIP --port 3306 --target-port 3306
```

```
# oc get service mariadb -o yaml
...
  selector:
    app: mariadb-server 1
    flavor.template.kubevirt.io/small: "true"
    ...
```

```
# oc get service,vmi,endpoints
```

```
# virtctl connect mariadb-server
```

```
# mysql_secure_installation
```




## 4- Verify the database connectivity.

Verify the database connectivity from the mariadb-client VM.

```
# virtctl console mariadb-client
```

Install telnet and nc packages to test the connection
```
# dnf install telnet mysql nc -y
```

```
# nc -zv mariadb-server 3306
```

```
# telnet mariadb-server 3306
```

```
mysql -uuser - h mariadb-server 
```

